23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 6, Chapter 18, Subchapter 7, is amended
24 to add an additional section to read as follows:
25 6-18-724. Ultra-processed food — Prohibition — Definition.
26 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
27 (1) Childhood obesity, morbidity, and wellness are matters of
28 statewide concern;
29 (2) Ultra-processed, industrially manufactured, nutrient-
30 depleted food with synthetic additives is undernourishing to students at
31 schools and contributes to childhood obesity; and
32 (3) A meal or snack offered to students at schools in this state
33 should be nutritious and made primarily of nutrient-dense plant or animal
34 products.
35 (b) As used in this section:
36 (1) "School" means:
