1 (A) A public school district;
2 (B) An open-enrollment public charter school; or
3 (C) A private school; and
4 (2) "Ultra-processed food" means a food or beverage that
5 contains one (1) or more of the following ingredients:
6 (A) Potassium bromate;
7 (B) Propylparaben;
8 (C) Titanium dioxide;
9 (D) Yellow dye 5;
10 (E) Yellow dye 6;
11 (F) Blue dye 1;
12 (G) Blue dye 2;
13 (H) Green dye 3;
14 (I) Red dye 3; or
15 (J) Red dye 40.
16 (c) A school shall not serve or sell on the school campus during the
17 normal school day ultra-processed food that is produced after January 1,
18 2028.
19 (d) This section does not prevent a parent, legal guardian, or person
20 standing in loco parentis to a student from providing ultra-processed food to
21 his or her child during the normal school day.
22 (e) The Department of Education may promulgate rules to implement this
23 section.
